******
[1] USA (South Dakota)
Date Thu 25 Sep 2014
Source: Keloland Television [summ., edited]
http://www.keloland.com/newsdetail.cfm/enterovirus-d68-confirmed-in-sd/?id=169832


A respiratory virus affecting children in many areas of the country has now been confirmed in South Dakota. The state health department says 7 of the samples sent in tested positive for enterovirus D68. All of the cases were west of the Missouri River, and those hit with the virus ranged in age from 11 months old to 19 years old. The previously uncommon EV-D68 can be serious for infants, children and teenagers, particularly children with asthma.

[Byline: Casey Wonnenberg]

