[No new features of significance have been reported. Enterovirus D68 remains associated with childhood disease except for very few older children and a single adult so far. The virus is no longer restricted to the Midwestern US and is likely to be identified throughout the whole of North America as diagnostic capability becomes generally available. It would be interesting to have information of the enteroviruses detected where enterovirus D68 appears to be absent or still rare. - Mod.CP

